Third Party Libraries
-----

Using code that you didn't write yourself, which could potentially be not secure.
Want to make sure if you're adding it to project, it's a good, trusted, well known, updated, secure library.


npm install -g nsp
nsp check # audit package.json
npm security auditing is now the default functionality of npm, and will give you warnings if security vulnerabilities are detected when adding packages.
use npm audit fix to fix detected security vulnerabilities. npm audit fix --force if absolutely necessary.


npm install -g snyk
snyk test # audit node_modules directory.